{"id": 7806, "title": "Ticket #7806: Simplify condor_dagman for command-line interface calls", "description": "<blockquote>\nIt would be really helpful if we could call <code>condor_dagman</code> more easily from the command line. Right now this is technically possible, but it requires a whole buch of input arguments that are usually provided in a .condor.sub file. If we could provide sensible defaults for these arguments, it would be easier to call <code>condor_dagman</code> for such purposes as gdb debugging, or allowing use cases like .dot file generation (as per <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7796\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7796'); return false;\" title=\"Add DAGMan -dot flag, to only write a .dot file without running jobs\">#7796</a></span>).\n\n<p>Ideally, we'd like to be able to make the following call:\n\n</p><p><code>condor_dagman mydag.dag</code>\n\n</p><p>There are probably all sorts of gotchas with this; I'll update the ticket once I've looked into it further.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2020-Oct-07 16:14</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=61446\">[61446]</a></span>: Fixed whitespace in status output (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7806\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7806'); return false;\" title=\"Simplify condor_dagman for command-line interface calls\">#7806</a></span>)  (By Mark Coatsworth )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2020-Oct-01 17:03</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\"